<exercise checkit-seed="0009" checkit-slug="V7" checkit-title="Basis of a subspace">
  <statement>
    <p>Consider the subspace <me>W=\operatorname{span}  \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
0 \\
0 \\
1 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
1 \\
-2 \\
1
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
-1 \\
1 \\
2
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
-4 \\
-2 \\
2
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-3 \\
-2 \\
0 \\
2
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-5 \\
-3 \\
-2 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] \right\} .</me></p>
    <ol>
      <li> Explain how to find a basis of <m>W</m>.</li>
      <li> Explain how to find the dimension of <m>W</m>.</li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <p>
      <me>\operatorname{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{cccccc}
0 &amp; 3 &amp; 1 &amp; -4 &amp; -3 &amp; -5 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; -1 &amp; -4 &amp; -2 &amp; -3 \\
1 &amp; -2 &amp; 1 &amp; -2 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 \\
-1 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 &amp; 2 &amp; 2 &amp; -1
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{cccccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; -\frac{7}{4} &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; -\frac{7}{8} &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; \frac{3}{8} &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; \frac{3}{16} &amp; 1
\end{array}\right] </me>
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>A basis of <m>W</m> is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
0 \\
0 \\
1 \\
-1
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
1 \\
-2 \\
1
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
1 \\
-1 \\
1 \\
2
\end{array}\right] , \left[\begin{array}{c}
-4 \\
-4 \\
-2 \\
2
\end{array}\right] \right\} </m>.</li>
      <li>The dimension of <m>W</m> is <m> 4 </m>.</li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

